description:
&lt;p&gt;The Sherwood Forest Hospitals NHS Foundation Trust is a successful, forward thinking organisation that is committed to providing high quality care to our patients.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Newark Hospital offers a fantastic range of out-patient clinics and we are continually working to expand and improve the services which we provide.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for an enthusiastic and committed health care assistant to join our small,friendly and supportive team. The role would suit an individual who is proactive, embraces change, has high standards and enjoys working with the public. They must have excellent communication skills and work collaboratively with all members of the multi-disciplinary team to achieve a positive patient experience.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful applicant must:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Have NVQ Level 2 or equivalent in care or a willingness to work towards.&lt;br /&gt;• Be able to demonstrate excellent communication skills.&lt;br /&gt;• Be able to work flexibly within the department when required&lt;br /&gt;• Have previous experience of working in a customer care role.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Sam Lambert, Department Sister on 01623 622515 ext 3902, Samantha.lambert3@nhs.net or Karen Meikle Department Sister on 01623 622515 ext 5841, Karen.meikle1@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
